(41861, 9, 'Class 9', 2, 'English', 1, 'Writing', 1, 'Essay Writing', '\r\n        \r\n        \r\n        <h2 style=\"line-height: 2; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Essay:</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">An essay is an exercise in composition Dr.Johnson defines an essay as a loose sally of the mind.Properly speaking,it is a written composition giving expression to one\'s own personal ideas or opinions on any topic.The literal meaning of essay is an abrupt.</p><h2 style=\"line-height: 2; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Different parts of an essay:</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Introduction:</span>&nbsp;It may be a simply a sentence or a very short paragraph.It may consist of a definatiion or a quotation,proverb,very brief story direct beginning general remarks or an abrupt beginning leading upto the subject.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Body:</span>&nbsp;This is the most important part of an essay because this is really the essay itself.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Conclusion:</span>&nbsp;As the introduction should arouse intrest the conclusion should satisfy it.A good conclusion consist of a suitable quotation.</p><h2 style=\"line-height: 2; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Characteristics of a good essay:</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Unity:</span>&nbsp;A good essay must have a unity, developing one subject with a definite end.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Balance:</span>&nbsp;The essay should follow a certain ordered line of thought and come to a definite conclusion. If there is a distance between introduction and conclusion, the essay loses its balance.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Coherence:</span>&nbsp;The idea developed in the essay should support one another logically to obtain coherence in the essay.It means one idea should lead to the next.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Length:</span>&nbsp;There can be no strict rules about length which depends upon the nature of the subjects.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Style:</span>&nbsp;The language and sentence should be simple direct and natural.Slang colloquial terms and free any easy should be your essay should be clear and communication.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Personal Touch:</span>&nbsp;Your essay should disclose your personal feelings and opinions.It should have yours individually in it.</p><h2 style=\"line-height: 2; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Steps of writing an essay:</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Planning:</span>&nbsp;Planning is a discovering and collecting all the relevant information about the essay.Planning is a key activity in writing any essay because better writing results in better plans.To plan the essay effectively you should consider the following questions:</p><ol style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"><li>Who is the reader?</li><li>What is the goal of writing an essay?</li><li>What is the basic message?</li><li>What constraints will affect the essay?</li><li>What format should be used?</li><li>How much time is allowed to ready the essay?</li></ol><h2 style=\"line-height: 2; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">Points to remember</h2><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">1. An essay is a composition on any subject and it has 3 parts:</p><ul style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"><li style=\"list-style: none;\">Introduction</li><li style=\"list-style: none;\">Body and</li><li style=\"list-style: none;\">Conclusion</li></ul><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">2. There are 5 steps of writing a good essay.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">3.&nbsp;Clearly define your subject in your essay.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">4. There are 4 types of essay.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">5. Write in a simple, concise and natural style.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">6. Divide your essay into several paragraphs.</p><p style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 0px; line-height: 2;\">7. Reading various subjects is very first fall for writing a good essay.</p>\r\n        \r\n        \r\n        												', '<b>Parts of an Essay:</b><br />\r\nIntroduction<br />\r\nBody<br />\r\nConclusion<br />\r\nCharacteristics of a good essay:<br />\r\nUnity<br />\r\nBalance<br />\r\nCoherence<br />\r\nLength<br />\r\nStyle<br />\r\nPersonal Touch<br />\r\nPoints to remember<br />\r\nIntroduction<br />\r\nBody <br />\r\nConclusion', '\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p1KbANXoWlo\"SPnextSP\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AYo6XGDe_z8\"', '\"Write main three parts of an Essay.\"SPnextSP\"Introduction, Body and Conclusion<br />\"'),
